Linux → Open-source operating system, widely used in servers and development
Windows → Proprietary operating system by Microsoft, widely used for personal and business desktops

Feature	                  Linux	                      Windows
Source Code	              Open-source	                Closed-source
Cost	                    Free	                      Paid license
Security	                More secure, fewer viruses	More vulnerable to malware
